postcontent: Savage 212 used once. Great gun but I now hunt in rifle territory. Have Leupold Ultimate Slam with BDC reticle which really makes a great combo.  Cabelas has the 212 listed @ $750 new  Ultimate slam @ $299 = $1,050 TOTAL.  I'd sell both for $900.  That's $150 off a gun that has only been used once target shooting on the range at the farm.  Plus I tested out every major brand of sabot slugs to find the ones that shot the best which were the 2 3/4" Federal's w/Barnes Expanders (you can see the grouping in my picture I posted)(this is another couple hundred dollar expense you can avoid since I did all the testing for you)  I also tested Winchester Supremes, Remington Accutips, Hornady, Brenneke you name it I spent probably $200 on every kind of sabot I could get my hands on & the Federal's shot the best out of this gun in particular.This is a really great shotgun for those who hunt in "shotgun only"  I had the 212's predecessor the 210F which was accurate as can be.  A friend of mind had the 210 before that & shot a deer @ 253 yards with the laser range finder (true story).  What can I say, the accutrigger is amazing.  The camo finish is great.  Ergonomics feel good in my hands.  Once sighted in this thing shoots where you point it & the BDC reticle on the Leupold scope works like a charm  I set mine to 200 yards and would feel confident shooting a whitetail at that range any day.Sadly right after I bought this gun I bought my own house with acreage in rifle territory and let's be honest... if I can use a rifle I'm going to.  But for those that are in "shotgun only" territory... this is the slugger for you.

postcontent: Several years ago my friends and I were talking about brotherhood and honor and courage and how we were raising our sons. As a result of that discussion we designed and made custom tsubas for authentic Katanas.
